{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Portable Body Sync",
  "description": "Syncs the portable-body/ directory with the living system, updates docs, and sends the weekly snapshot email. Can be run independently or as part of the Friday calibration.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Invoke the portable-body-maintainer agent to run a full portable body sync.\\n\\nProtocol: ~/shared/portable-body/agents/portable-body-maintainer.md (also at ~/.kiro/agents/body-system/portable-body-maintainer.md)\\n\\nSteps:\\n1. Read the portable-body-maintainer agent definition for the full protocol\\n2. Read ~/shared/context/active/portable-layer.md for the file manifest\\n3. Sync all portable files from their source locations to portable-body/\\n4. Detect new files that should be included (new agents, hooks, steering, tools, research, specs)\\n5. Update README.md, CHANGELOG.md, and SANITIZE.md in portable-body/\\n6. Send the weekly snapshot email to richscottwill@gmail.com\\n7. Report what changed, what was added, and any portability gaps detected\\n\\nDoomsday mentality: operate as if the DevSpace will be deleted tomorrow. When in doubt, include the file."
  }
}